#. <section class="sutta" id="sn42.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga"
msgstr "1. Chiefs"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Caṇḍasutta → caṇḍagāmaṇisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn42.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Caṇḍasutta"
msgstr "1. Vicious"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.305"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho caṇḍo gāmaṇi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho caṇḍo gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the chief named Fury went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and said to him:"

#. VAR: yena midhekacco caṇḍo caṇḍotveva → yena midhekacco caṇḍoteva (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena midhekacco caṇḍo caṇḍotveva "
"saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some people are regarded as "
"furious,"

#. VAR: yena midhekacco sorato soratotveva → yena midhekacco suratoteva (bj) | yena midhekacco sūratoteva (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.1:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena midhekacco sorato soratotveva saṅkhaṃ "
"gacchatī”ti?"
msgstr "while others are regarded as sweet-natured?”"

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.5"
msgid "“Idha, gāmaṇi, ekaccassa rāgo appahīno hoti."
msgstr "“Take someone who hasn’t given up greed."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.6"
msgid "Rāgassa appahīnattā pare kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they get annoyed by others, and they show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.7"
msgid "So caṇḍotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as furious."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.8"
msgid "Doso appahīno hoti."
msgstr "They haven’t given up hate."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.9"
msgid "Dosassa appahīnattā pare kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they get annoyed by others, and they show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.10"
msgid "So caṇḍotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as furious."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.11"
msgid "Moho appahīno hoti."
msgstr "They haven’t given up delusion."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.12"
msgid "Mohassa appahīnattā pare kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they get annoyed by others, and they show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.13"
msgid "So caṇḍotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as furious."

msgctxt "sn42.1:1.14"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, gāmaṇi, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena midhekacco caṇḍo caṇḍotveva "
"saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"This is the cause, this is the reason why some people are regarded as "
"furious."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.1:2.1"
msgid "Idha pana, gāmaṇi, ekaccassa rāgo pahīno hoti."
msgstr "But take someone who has given up greed."

# reading akopiyamano
msgctxt "sn42.1:2.2"
msgid ""
"Rāgassa pahīnattā pare na kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ na pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they don’t get annoyed by others, and don’t show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.3"
msgid "So soratotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as sweet-natured."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.4"
msgid "Doso pahīno hoti."
msgstr "They’ve given up hate."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.5"
msgid ""
"Dosassa pahīnattā pare na kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ na pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they don’t get annoyed by others, and don’t show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.6"
msgid "So soratotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as sweet-natured."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.7"
msgid "Moho pahīno hoti."
msgstr "They’ve given up delusion."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.8"
msgid ""
"Mohassa pahīnattā pare na kopenti, parehi kopiyamāno kopaṃ na pātukaroti."
msgstr "So they don’t get annoyed by others, and don’t show it."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.9"
msgid "So soratotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "They’re regarded as sweet-natured."

msgctxt "sn42.1:2.10"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, gāmaṇi, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena midhekacco sorato soratotveva "
"saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is the cause, this is the reason why some people are regarded as sweet-"
"natured.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.306"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.1:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, caṇḍo gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the chief named Fury said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn42.1:3.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn42.1:3.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo "
"pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn42.1:3.4"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn42.1:3.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn42.1:3.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
